[49m[38;5;10m+    1226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 4: Combine into an Ensemble
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The empirical lesson from FluSight and the COVID-19 Forecast Hub is that ensembles outperform individual models. The combiner takes per-model forecasts, weighs them by recent calibration performance (or equal-weights as the cold-start fallback), and produces a Vincentized quantile combination that preserves calibration properties.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m class EnsembleCombiner:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """Vincentized quantile combiner with WIS-weighted weights.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The Vincentized combination averages quantile values across
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     models rather than averaging across distributions. For a
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     grid of probability levels q1, q2, ..., qN, the ensemble
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     quantile at qi is the weighted average of the per-model
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     quantile values at qi. This preserves the ensemble's
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     calibration properties.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Production replaces the demo's simplified WIS-weighting with
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     a continuously-updated calibration tracker that pulls coverage
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     history from the Aurora registry and discards models with
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     recent calibration failures.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     def __init__(self, config):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         self.config = dict(config)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     def _compute_weights(self, per_model_forecasts, calibration_history):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         """Return weights per model for the Vincentized combination."""
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         method = self.config["method"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         n = len(per_model_forecasts)
